Introduction

Lew is a South Korean rapper, singer, and lyricist under Yue Hua Entertainment.

In 2016, Lew made his first public appearance in the variety program "Hello Counselor" as a teenager seeking for advice. His good looks and kind nature instantly made him a crowd favorite, and resulted with him being scouted by several entertainment agencies.

In 2017, Lew then appeared and competed in the second season of Mnet's hit survival show Produce 101, where he was eliminated in episode 10 after ranking 23rd place.

The same year, he made his official debut as half of the duo HyeongseopXEuiwoong, along fellow labelmate and group member Hyeongseop. They debuted on November 2, 2017, with the release of the digital single "The Moment of Memory".

On January 3, 2022, Lew was revealed as the first member of Yue Hua Entertainment's upcoming boy group TEMPEST. He debuted as a member of the group on March 2, 2022, with the release of their first mini album titled "It's ME, It's WE".
